teamnoir <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udangor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dangor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/02 4:04:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=224>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Druids with increased healing skills?</span><hr size=1> I agree with this and disagree.  As a high end cleric I find that it is very difficult to get into groups in most high lvl areas due to the fact that druids and shaman can handle the role of a cleric well enough and still have other uses in the group.  <br>
<br>
However I can see the usefulness of a druid having increased heals on raids.  <br>
<br>
I understand wanting to have the epic changed and agree fully.  I like the ideas of having a cold based version of ro's.  However I find it upsetting that any common druid at post 55 lvls could have increased healing abilities to further put clerics out of a job when it comes to simple exp groups.  Most high lvl guilds at the high end game put in good time to getting AA points and I could understand a few Druid Class AA abilities being ones that could increase heals.  As for giving Druids teleportation abilities on the moon, while I can understand the IC reasons for the wizzies having the market on this I would like to see druids with them as well.  On the subject of PotG and Aego/blessing of aego stacking, I would rather have the druid have to recast PotG for themselves then have to recast blessing on a group of people who didnt click off PotG and I'm sure it will happen based on the amount of times enchanters had to recast C3 when they had stacking issues with C and C2.  I like the idea of the single target potg and perhaps have it not be overwritten by aego.  For the most part I wish you all well in getting your changes into the game.  <br>
<br>
Dangor Thanos<br>
High Priest of The Stoic<br>
Povar Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ufenrillikesdadead.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FenrilLikesDaDead</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(4/9/02 4:05:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgroverants.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=650.topic&index=225>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A compromise</span><hr size=1> After reading the petition (Christmas Wish List) I would have to disagree with it and say no.  I have several reasons for doing so, but first let me tell you about my main.  I play a necromancer and for the past two months I have busted my butt to get him up to level 36.  The members of the guild I belong to are thoroughly impressed that I have leveled as fast as I did.  <br>
First, as a Necromancer I will not be called on any raids unless it's guild sponsored.  This is due the fact that I refuse to be someone's twitch whore.  My pet is fairly effective and my offensive spells are pretty good.  <br>
Second, in the process of leveling as fast as I have I made my character a group character suitable in groups only.  I don't fear kite and solo.  In doing so I have managed to show those that have 50+ level characters who are playing their alts at my level and peoples mains my level that a necromancer is a very viable group class.  <br>
Third, if you want to talk about balancing then give Necros the ability to port into undead zones only and make sure VI gives us at least apprehensively faction with Mistmoor etc.. so that way we don't die upon porting.  <br>
Fourth, my heal spells are more mana efficient than even a clerics but the downside is that it literally kills me.  I've played healer in a group with my necro and there were times that I was killed because I healed too much when the main assist pulled too much.  The downside to a necro is yes we can heal, but it takes up most of our mana and our health.  This makes life tapping unusable because we used our mana to heal.<br>
Fifth, my necro has mastery in offense and defense, very good in dodge, and excellent in piercing yet even a cleric out damages me in melee.  This is a serious inbalance when considering that said cleric hasn't meleed hardly at and doesn't have the skills I do.  Part of the drawbacks to my class and I live with it.  Due to my high levels in melee I am often put in charge of defending the clerics and assist the tank.  When the tank calls for zone run I stay behind and cover the other casters escape.  Sometimes I die and sometimes I don't.  If these other casters don't follow the order for the zone run after 10 or 15 seconds of being called I run for the zone.  Reason being is that usually the tank is dead and the majority of my group is also.  <br>
My job also entails doing a corpse recovery no matter how many died or where they died.  The worst CR I've ever done to date was the night before necros got the lesser summon corpse spell and we were in the gobbie mines in LOIO.  The party, except for me, died down in there deep next to the gobbie lord and his pet.  I spent three hours recovering 5 corpses and the reason why it took so long was because I couldn't have track corpse and gather shadows up at the same time while underground/dungeons.  I spent those hours wandering around in an area I didn't have a map for invised with no track corpse.  A drawback, but also earned me quite a few good friends that knew that they could count on me to get them out of a difficult spot.  <br>
The basic moral of this is simple: Learn to play your class within your limitations and use your strengths to the best advantage given to you.  BTW one of my very good friends is a 42nd level druid and she wasted a few hours buffing me, porting me around etc... so I could complete the early stages of my epic.  Also Shamans and Druids are my best friend because of hit point regen.  When I get that I become a mana battery due to my Allure of Death line of spells, which makes me have less downtime between pulls so I can nuke/dot/slow the mobs that are pulled and the tanks don't suffer as much damage.  Which turns means the cleric saves more mana because they heal less and the healing gets spread around to the druids/shamans that I'm grouped with.  It's matter of tactics pure and simple.  Instead of concentrating on solo tactics I developed group tactics and all of the groups that I been with have commented on how well I help out to drop the mobs we're facing.  <br>
The choice is yours on how you want to play with your limitations.  From all the posts above in this thread necros are mentioned hardly at all because most ppl that are non-necros have never had the pleasure of grouping with one.  Druids actually have a better chance of getting into a group than a necro of any level.  I get groups really easy because I have busted my ass to earn other peoples respect in my abilities to play my class and the way I will readily die for them so they can get away.<br>
/rant off<br>
Fenril Likesdadead<br>
36th Level Necromancer<br>
