Nature's Recovery gives 900HP for 250 Mana in 3 Minutes (with no side-affects).<br>
<br>
Being slowed and snared for 24 seconds has never caused me a problem or caused Tanks around me problems. It is a brief irritation but allows the spell to be a little more powerful in its healing than otherwise it could be. <br>
To balance that I would feel it would be fair to reduce the time over which Nature's Recovery takes effect. I feel personally that lowering it to 24 seconds make its rather too much like Torpor and would prefer to see it as 1 minute, but that's me.<br>
<br>
Of course Druid's get Nature's Touch at 60 too, which gives 978 HP for 400 Mana instantly (well 5.5 seconds casting). Compare this to Chloroblast at 428 Hp for 175 Mana in 3 seconds, or Superior Heal (which by 60 is 9 levels old), 583 for 250 mana in 4.5 seconds.  <br>
I cannot for the life of me understand why Nature's Touch is such a bad spell. You can cast chloroblast twice in about the same time for more efficient healing (and importantly land the first heal in less time). I think that either NT must be made faster casting to offset its high cost and bad ratio or it must be made cheaper in mana or better in healing. Add in the sheer number of fizzles and the picture just gets worse. I've always felt that CB was a great heal, being so fast and efficient even if it is not too big. NT should be our upgrade to SH, our big, long casting heal. SH has a ratio of 2.33 hps per mana so around 3 would be about where I see NT, so keeping it at 400 mana it should heal somewhere in the 1200 range. Alternatively it could drop to 4 seconds casting, 900 HPs, 300 mana but I prefer the former as a solution.<br>
<br>
