&quot;Insane possibilites &lt;Slow, Torpor, cann&gt;&quot;  True druids have none of these.. neither do clerics.  Why should you get them and not me?<br>
<br>
&quot;Druids are asking to be fixed in &lt;REALLY high end situations&gt; only &lt;NToV, Vindi, etc&gt;&quot;  I'll give you ground on the concept that that is why you started the petition; but the reality is, changing the class changes the class...  it's really hard to tweak you to be a &quot;make or break&quot; class in raids and not have it effect the game play.  And, not to beat a dead horse, why do you deserve to get that status, I bet necros have you beat on the end game issues.....Oh, oh.. revised since the person I am replying on this to went so far as to say &quot;if you are not rebutting... petition.. examples... relating to this &lt;end game&gt; particular mode of play, *YOU CAN SAVE YOURSELF THE ENERGY SINCE YOUR REBUTTAL SIMPLY DOESN'T APPLY AND THEREFORE DOESN'T MATTER*&quot;  Riiiight....  you can make all these magical changes and the only thing it has an effect on are raids.. what, cast a heal and if there aren't 60 ppl in the zone it won't go off????  sorry, the doesn't matter thing pissed me off.  It is absurd to think that you can change the &quot;End Game&quot; without thinking it will effect the general high level play.<br>
<br>
&quot;Have you looked at the buffing and healing abilities of clerics lately&quot;  Lets look at this... Buffs:  Cleric, Kunark:  Heroism (good), Heroic Bond (still use at 59), Symbol of Marzin (good for main tank, but sucks the Peridots - Druid buffs take reagents?), Naltron's Mark (Great spell), Bulwark (pre ageo this is a must have), Ageis (worthless);  Velious:  Ageolism (exceptional and simple for the important tanks); Luclin:  Blessing of Ageo (amazing spell, and amazingly rare), Marzin's Mark (never met someone with this).  Druid, Kunark:  Circle of Winter/Summer (really good for resists, esp on a pvp server), Regrowth (good regen), Girdle of Karana (+str is good), Nature Skin (better than Herosim), two group damage shields, regrowth of the grove (amazing group regen); Velious:  Protection of the Glades (been over this one already);  Luclin:  Spirit of the Eagle (amazing - but travel not combat based), Circle of the Seasons (yeah it replaces SoW/S but cleric buffs go obsolete too).  <br>
  Now lets go into heals:  Clerics, Kunark:  Remedy (good for kunark, patch heal after - great range), Divine light (again good for kunark, but too slow to be reliable in Vel/luc), Celestial Elixir (this is truly an amazing spell).  Velious:  Celestial Healing (nice filler till I hit 59). Luclin:  Blessing of Ageolism (Really good spell in that it lessens mana cost and Perdiot loss, but not by much).  Druids:  Kunark:  Superior Healing (good at the time but gets outdated in a mana/hp/cast time ratio I believe),  Chloroblast (equals remedy except in range), Natures Recovery (slow Celestial line), Nature's Touch (slightly less mana efficient than Divine Light).<br>
  So, from a heal base, we don't seem IMO to be that far off, and aside from a single target PotG, I think our buffs are fairly consistent as well....<br>
<br>
&quot;Gimped Druids&quot;  How does a CotH mage effect travel?  Do they stand at every zone line and offer to summon you for nothing?  Every mage I know hates having to summon someone who isn't coming in behind on a raid or truly lost in a confusing zone.  And.. if we wanna talk CotH, shouldn't you throw mages a bone as they get replaced by nercros using summon corpse, since most of luclin doesn't let you use Call???  You are arguing single (and by definition I assume pickup) groups, which I take to mean groups that take 6 people who fit a mold well, and go kill stuff.  Sure it's not ideal, but only a moron holds the group back because they don't have the perfect combo.. heck I've been in OS with 3 mages a necro and an enchanter, does that sound like an ideal group?  p.s.  it takes (best case) 15 minutes to port up to the moon and down again, and that assumes that you got to the nexus 20 seconds before it zapped you up.<br>
<br>
&quot;Druid heals post 50 = 2.2 hp/mana&quot;  Remedy is 2.7 hp per mana, Divine light is 2.6, so we didn't go up either (and no, group heals don't count).<br>
<br>
Anyway... I am sorry and it got late, I made it halfway through page 7.  The common consensus seems to be that Druids (and as a frighteningly few people pointed out Shamen) need to be reavamped when it comes to heals considering endgame.  Thats all fine and well, but please don't argue for it whithout considering that Clerics need the revamp as well...<br>
