<br>
<br>
I have 3 different approaches to adjusting our class to make them better without taking away from the other classes...<br>
<br>
Make our skin buffs MORE POWERFUL than cleric buffs.<br>
<br>
Changes might be:<br>
<br>
Level   Spell              AC       HP        Regen   Mana   Dur<br>
1         SLW               4         30                             27m<br>
14       SLR                8        100                             27m<br>
24       SLS               12       160           2                36m<br>
34       SLD               16       220           2         1      54m<br>
44       SLN               20       250           2         2     1h 12m<br>
52       NatureSkin      24       400           4         2     1h 24m<br>
60       PoTG             28       750           6         6      2h 30m<br>
<br>
This breakdown...  We exceed cleric &quot;straight&quot; buffs at all points.  With regen and mana regen, we would offer superior BUFFING -- allowing us to contribute in a better fashion.<br>
<br>
Aegolism could be used but, if you went with our spells, clerics could then tack on their Symbols and AC spells ontop of our base spells, providing overall better protection and some regen -- not massive, but good enough to make them worth stacking.<br>
<br>
Just adjust the spell levels as shown to provide these levels of protection.<br>
<br>
Not a second string cleric.  A buff person with fire and cold plus HP and AC.<br>
<br>
As for epic, add a step to the process to change the proc.  Set proc to DOT and Ro's Smoldering debuff combined.  <br>
<br>
This would make it a very effective and desirable tool without unbalancing anything.  The DOT does damage still while the debuff adds to it's use in group situations.  Keeping it both along the lines we currently have for spells and letting us offer even more in groups with melee debuffing.<br>
<br>
IMHO these suggestions beat the hell out of &quot;gimme more wimpy healing abilities&quot; and &quot;just dump the snare from our epic&quot;.<br>
<br>
