<br>
You asked for a better direct heal above natures touch (880 vs clerics 960). I can also qoute a number of druids who posted lines like &quot;Try to heal a 7k tank and see how much it does&quot;. Now, if you try to heal a tank with 7k hp who is NOT tanking then you should have NO issues at all. He takes as example 2k in riposte (why he is so stupid to take them in the first place we can argue but he got them anyway). That is (as you already stuck regen on him right?) ~3 Natures touch on him for 1200m in ~21 sec. Would a CH cost less mana? Yup. Does that render druids usless? Nope. Does that mean a druid cant heal as good as a Cleric? Yup.<br>
<br>
Now, let me try to put this to you again, you are NOT suppose to be healing the all the MTs damage (but you do a damn nice job as patch healing as secondary healer), some druids relize that some dont (or we would not have people asking for healing for a 7k tank).  You are not suppose to be healing the rampage tanks constantly either. You are not suppose to alone replace a cleric (even though druids do that today in exp groups). You are suppose to heal riposte damage (which people at this level should learn to reduce to close to nothing with positioning), potential AoE damage (which in many cases is avoidable or easy to counteract with group regen depending on if we talk NToV or Ssra) and similar damage.You want to talk about Burrower, AoW etc? How many people are there exactly taking damage on those encounters for you that you need to heal up huge amounts of damage? And also ask yourself, if you had the cleric heals (960 vs 880 80pt more 1 sec faster heal) and CH (10500 4.5 sec longer casting time) how would you exactly make someone survive that overaggroed? Are you seriously trying to tell me that one cleric can keep someone who aggroed and tanking up long enough for the MT to get aggro again? Because you are saying you cant and I would say, well neither can a cleric so what is the deal? Or are you saying that your tanks/casters are constantly taking damage from burrower rampage/riposte and you need to heal them? Because if they do take such constant damage then I really wonder what they are doing (and a hint would then be to go to the ranger board and learn about aggro management)...<br>
<br>
You see, here is the problem I got, the group heal suggested is a joke. It is simply to good but do something like 25% of buffed hp for 900m or so that is enough to keep up with AoE damage (and dont affect a regular exp group as a sidenote). Some complained they get AoE damage, that is funny as I had druids hold a group of melee standing ALONE with problems but it is doable. Give him a paladin, the benefit of AoE mana song, and they will do great. Also you can tell your random tank to please step out of the AoE range if he takes to much damage so you cant keep up. Slightly less DPS but cost more mana to rebuff him if he dies and he can bind wound if nothing else and charge back in. Is it perfect? Nope but it is sure doable. Perhaps level up the raid or get better resists if you cant do it. But that is a sidenote anyhow.<br>
<br>
If you want big direct heals then I got to ask what are you going to give up for it? As you want to go over the line of what clerics been doing best (big direct heals) to do it better then clerics. Clerics dont get snare, invis, track, dots etc. We do get the best heals ingame though. Also you people keep saying this is to fix the raiding end game. Well here comes a wake up call, what ever &quot;fix&quot; you suggest affects BOTH exping and end level raiding. Druids are easily replacing clerics these days in exp groups. You dont have to heal someone for 7k only because he has 7k hp, you only have to heal as much as he takes in damage, that is a important difference. And the bigger heals a druids get the more he steps in on the clerics healing territory. And before I get to hear someone say well you dont know high end level raiding, AoW kill, clearing of NToV, Ssra Creator and Arch etc. Yes, I am there, Yes I got druids there and Yes, they do contribute. <br>
<br>
The once who wrote up this petition also seem to lack the following:<br>
1. Actually read what other classes got and the exact effect of it (The dot is a good example)<br>
2. Remember that yes raiding at the end game is fun but a class do pay for abilities through out the whole carrier. That means having it easy early levels can mean beeing less wanted at higher levels.<br>
3. Trying to secure a wide base for it by suggesting something that dont make a class god like...<br>
<br>
<br>
There are issues I agree, but look at that list, compare what would happend if you got it all. Compare what you got and what other classes got, you aint exactly in a bad shape. As for all the druids posting they agree, from what I see so is only 10% even 60... You should perhaps clean out your own house of the people who are not high end raiding and posted before complaining over other coming here and posting that aint high end raiding.<br>
<br>
